               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18401123-name-787" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-787" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-787" type="surname" value="MURRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-787" type="given" value="GEORGE THOMAS"></interp>GEORGE THOMAS MURRAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I work for Mr. Richard Claxton and his partner, they are cotton-manufacturers. Kelly worked for them at their factory in Hoxton—Ashton keeps a stall for the sale of iron and other things—on the 14th of November I saw Kelly at his stall offering him a brass cog-wheel—he asked him 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for it—Ashton said, "No, take it away, I don't want it"—Kelly said, "Do give mo a penny"—Ashton gave him 1<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and put the wheel in his pocket—Kelly then went and bought 1<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. worth of apples.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18401123-name-788" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-788" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-788" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401123-name-788" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD NEWMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the prosecutor's service. Murray told me what he had seen—I informed my master, who sent me to Ashton's stall to see if the wheel was exposed for sale, and it was not—we sent for the policeman, and I went with him to Ashton's stall—the officer asked him where the wheel was that he bought of Murray, and he took it out of his pocket—he said he bought it of the boy for 1<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—it is worth about half-a-crown—I went to the loft where the machinery lies—I produce the bear<lb></lb>ing that it was taken from.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Ashton's Defence.</hi> I told the boy three times I would not have it—I put it into my pocket to take it home, and try to find where the boy came from.</p>
